The disease does its job: an immeasurable weakness prevents him from going to the toilet alone and even eating himself.
Sitting at the table in front of a delicious lunch, he resigns to let himself be helped with food.
Courageously, he even manages to smile and talk to the strangers who are busy around him, bring him his medications, and offer him a bath.
The Courage of Ordinary Death.
“My biggest wish is to cure my diarrhea because it’s humiliating,” he said.
