Facts about Sexually Transmitted Infections
What are the most important sexually transmitted diseases?
Bacterial STIs include syphilis, chlamydia and tripper (gonorrhea).
Common viral STIs are HIV, human papillomaviruses, herpes genitalis or hepatitis.
Filzlauses and crabs are among the parasitic STIs.
Who are the main affected groups?
Syphilis and trippers occur mainly in men who have sex with men.
The Robert Koch Institute estimates that at least four out of five of all cases of syphilis reported in Germany are transmitted through sexual contact between men.
In heterosexual adults, chlamydia, trichomonads, candidiasis, trippers and human papillomaviruses are common sexually transmitted diseases.
